  "notes": "Faroese (føroyskt). ~50,000 speakers in Faroe Islands. Old West Norse descent alongside Icelandic, but more innovative. ⟨á⟩ = [ɔa] (cf. Icelandic á = [au]); ⟨ð⟩ → [j] or [∅] between vowels (weakening); ⟨g⟩ → [w] before back vowels, [j] elsewhere. Preaspiration present (⟨pp tt kk⟩ = [ʰp ʰt ʰk]). No voiceless sonorants (unlike Icelandic). Danish administrative language until 1948; heavy Danish loanwords. Source: Árnason (2011), Hanssen (2010).",
